Text:
It's so annoying...watching the construction trudge
along...

If we used slime, we could build something like
this...in half a day...

If a new company building suddenly pops up in half a
day, the surrounding companies will definitely find it
suspicious.

I understand how you feel, Eta, but we'll need to
match the pace of the outside world in this matter.

It's already reckless enough from an outside
perspective to rush through construction in
two months.

Then...after two months, let me build it in half
a day. It'll be more fun...and more logical.

You're just being antagonistic for the sake of it,
aren't you!
Yeah, of course, I am...*yawn*
Seriously, Eta...

(Still, thanks to Eta's architectural expertise, the
construction of our new company base is moving
along steadily.)
(The best thing I can currently do...)

(Is...leave what I can't do to the others until I can
handle it myself, or delegate someone to decide
a course of action.)

...Can I...reduce the construction period by a week
or so...?

...No. It must be completed in exactly two months and
made to look as if we barely managed it in time.
...You're such a stickler, Gamma.
I'm not a stickler!
...That concludes Lady Gamma's report.
Thank you, Lambda.
So there have been no attacks on Gamma since then...

None. However, as it's happened once, something
similar may likely occur again.

Indeed. In fact, they may make a more straightforward
approach to take down Luna, Ltd.
A straightforward approach...?

They may attempt to ruin our credibility as a
commercial company and make it impossible
for us to do business in the capital.

For example, we'll soon complete Luna, Ltd.'s new
commercial complex...

But what will happen if the facility doesn't
function as planned?
It will be seen as a major setback for Luna, Ltd.

A loss of credibility will also lead to a sharp drop
in the company's share prices, which have seen a
meteoric recovery and rise.

So what measures do you think our rival companies
will take to ensure this happens?

Perhaps they will somehow interfere with the supply
of Luna, Ltd.'s products...?!

Yes, that would be the most effective way. Most
businesses will cease to operate without their
products.
Should we place our supply chain on high alert, then?
I suppose...

...but simply remaining on the defensive wouldn't be
much fun.

We may as well use this opportunity to bid farewell
to our meddling rivals.
So we'll be going on the offensive.

Yes. First, let's have Beta and Zeta gather the
necessary intel within the capital.

Then based on that intel...we'll move to make our
counterattack!
